      "note_no": "39",
      "note": "This refers to the legal punishment for homicide, termed qisas (\"just retribution\") and explained in 2:178 and the corresponding notes. In the present context, the term wall (\"protector\" or \"defender of [one's] rights\") is usually taken to mean the heir or next of kin of the victim; Zamakhshari, however, observes that it may also apply to the government (as-sultan): an interpretation which is obviously based on the concept of the government as the \"protector\" or \"defender of the rights\" of all its citizens. As regards the expression qutila mazlaman (\"slain wrongfully\"), it is obvious that it refers only to cases of wilful homicide, since the concept of zulm applies in the Qur'an exclusively to intentional and never to accidental wrongdoing."
