    {
      "note_no": "41",
      "note": "I.e., he is avenged in this world by the retribution exacted from his murderer, and in the life to come, blessed by the special grace which God bestows on all who have been slain without any legal or moral justification (Razi). Some of the commentators, however, relate the pronoun \"he\" to the defender of the victim's rights, respectively, to the latter's heir or next of kin, and explain the above phrase as meaning \"he is sufficiently helped by the law of just retribution (qisas) and should not, therefore, demand any punishment in excess of what is equitable\"."
